            <p style='font-size:15px;padding:5px;width:auto' class="text-base">Pakiza is situated in the heart of Ujjain, a stone's throw away from the most important intersection of this city's Ghantaghar or the tower square. This place began the mall culture in Ujjain with a superstore that is basically an extension of the Indore-based retail group Pakiza. Iqbal Gori, who was just a cycle-puncture repairer in the 1970s, made Pakiza a superstore from a cloth stall. He succeeded in life as he always believed in customer satisfaction. The group still follows the same motto, and thus, on top of the features of a regular department store, Pakiza does offer something more to its customers. Mehndi/henna design, popcorn, and cold drinks are some of the free offerings here for every shopper.</p>
